The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 5: Officials from India and Mauritius met here today to negotiate changes in the double taxation treaty to try plug tax loopholes. Though finance ministry officials remained tight lipped about the content and outcome of the talks which they described as routine, sources said talks on renegotiating parts of the treaty have been initiated but final results are yet to emerge. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 5: Mahindra amp; Mahindra will invest Rs 400 crore in the next two to two-and-half years on capacity expansion, including a greenfield plant. We have been gradually increasing our farm equipment manufacturing capacities of our different plants and in the next two to two-and-half years, we will invest Rs 400 crore on these and new product developments, M amp;M president (farm equipment) A. Choudhari said. 

 Ras al Khamiah (UAE), Oct. 5: Ashok Leyland, the Hinduja group flagship, is setting up a $5 million bus assembly unit in the UAE. This will be gradually upgraded to a vehicle assembly plant for trucks and buses. An MoU to set up the unit was signed here today between Ashok Leyland and the Ras al Khaimah Investment Authority.

 New Delhi, Oct. 5: Metlife India Insurance today said it may infuse Rs 450 crore capital to sustain the 100 per cent year-on-year growth and increase agent force to 50,000 and double branch network in the next two years.




